t the\nphysical processes responsible for truncating star formation in galaxies are\nnot restricted to the rare, rich cluster environment, but are viable in much\nmore common environments. In particular, we conclude that ram pressure\nstripping or cluster-induced starbursts cannot be solely responsible for the\nlow star formation rates in these systems.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 17 Jul 2002 14:41:51 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-07"}
